      "content": "When your residuals are skewed and have outliers, you can try several approaches. First, you might consider transforming your dependent variable, like using a log transformation, to help normalize the distribution. You could also try addressing the outliers directly, perhaps by winsorizing them or using robust regression methods. If the skewness is severe, checking for non-linear relationships with your predictors and adding polynomial terms could also be beneficial.",
