    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i tried the log transform but the residuals are still looking pretty messy in some parts of the distribution. it's like there are these specific points that just don't belong and they're pulling the whole model off. what's a more robust way to handle those huge deviations without just deleting data?",
