    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If the outliers are really skewing your results, consider using robust regression techniques like M-estimators or Theil-Sen regression. These methods are designed to be less sensitive to extreme values than standard Ordinary Least Squares (OLS). Alternatively, you could use a Generalized Linear Model (GLM) with a different error distribution, such as a Gamma or Tweedie distribution, which are often better suited for positively skewed data like housing prices.",
      "source": "target",
