      "content": "To pinpoint the source of those chaotic outliers, you can employ leverage analysis and influence measures. Cook's distance is a classic tool that tells you how much the regression coefficients change when a specific data point is removed. You can also examine standardized residuals alongside leverage values to see if the outliers are both far from the predicted line and are extreme in terms of their predictor values. This helps you understand if the point is an error, a genuine extreme case, or just an influential one.",
